Cholera, single case - USA (Minnesota) 990528000140
[1
Date: Fri, 28 May 1999 08:13:05 -0400
From: Paul Blake <PAB1@dhr.state.ga.us>

Was this case of cholera caused by toxigenic _Vibrio cholerae_ O1 or O139?
In the past there has been considerable confusion because some people have
non-O1 Vibrio cholerae infections, which should not be called cholera.
Another possible source of confusion is that non-toxigenic _V. cholerae_ O1
strains exist.
If it has not been done already, the isolate should be sent to CDC for
definitive identification.
Were the snails eaten raw? Where did they come from?
--
Paul Blake, MD, MPH
Acting State Epidemiologist
Georgia
e-mail: PAB1@dhr.state.ga.us
