[3
Date: Fri, 28 May 1999 09:20:18 CDT
From: Kirk Smith <smithk1@mdh-dpc.health.state.mn.us>

Regarding the "cholera" case in Minnesota that was just posted, the
patient's isolate was a non-O1, non-O139 serogroup /_Vibrio cholera_/;
Benenson's "Control of Communicable Diseases Manual" states that reporting
such cases as cholera "is inaccurate and leads to confusion". We attempted
to reach the patient regarding the case but were unsuccessful.
--
Kirk Smith, DVM, PhD
Minnesota Department of Health
